==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Moslem
<hw>Mos"lem</hw> <pr>(m⟦ocr⟧z"l⟦ecr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Moslems</plw> <pr>(m⟦ocr⟧z"l⟦ecr⟧mz)</pr>,
<xex>or collectively</xex> <plw>Moslem</plw>.</plu> <ety>[Ar.
<ets>muslim</ets> a true believer in the Muslim faith, fr.
<ets>salama</ets> to submit to God, to resign one's self to the divine
will. Cf. <er>Islam</er>, <er>Mussulman</er>.]</ety> <def>An adherent of
Islam; a Mussulman; an orthodox Muslim.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>muslim</asp>.]</altsp> ⟦ldquo⟧Heaps of slaughtered
<xex>Moslem</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They piled the ground with <qex>Moslem</qex> slain.</q>
<rj><qau>Halleck.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 947 --></p>

<p><ent>Moslem</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Moslem
<hw>Mos"lem</hw> <pr>(m⟦ocr⟧z"l⟦ecr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or
